In order to install the UNIX System, you must reserve a partition (a portion
of your hard disk's space) on your primary hard disk for the UNIX System.
After you press 'ENTER', you will be shown a screen that will allow you to
create new partitions, delete existing partitions or change the active
partition of your primary hard disk (the partition that your computer will
boot from).

WARNING:  All files in any partition(s) you delete will be destroyed.
If you wish to attempt to preserve any files from an existing UNIX System, do
not delete its partition(s).

